Package warehouse

Interface IObservable<TYPE>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IWarehouseObservable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Warehouse
    public interface IObservable<TYPE>
    Interface that specifies the behavior of objects that are observable. It specifies that IListeners can be registered and unregistered. Registered IListeners are notified about changes.
    Author:
    OOP

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      void registerListener​(IListener<TYPE> listener)
      Registers an IListener at the IObservable (if it is not already registered).
      void unregisterListener​(IListener<TYPE> listener)
      Unregisters the IListener at the IObservable.

    • Method Detail

      • registerListener

        void registerListener​(IListener<TYPE> listener)
        Registers an IListener at the IObservable (if it is not already registered).
        Parameters:
        listener - the IListener that should be registered

      • unregisterListener

        void unregisterListener​(IListener<TYPE> listener)
        Unregisters the IListener at the IObservable. The IListener is only unregistered if it is currently registered at the IObservable.
        Parameters:
        listener - the IListener that should be unregistered
